We can write
\begin{align*}
\left| \frac{\beta - \alpha}{1 - \overline{\alpha} \beta} \right| &= \frac{|\beta - \alpha|}{|1 - \overline{\alpha} \beta|} \\
&= \frac{|1 - \overline{\alpha} \beta|}{|1 - \overline{\alpha} \beta|} \cdot \frac{|\beta - \alpha|}{|1 - \overline{\alpha} \beta|} \\
&= \frac{|(\beta - \alpha)(1 - \overline{\alpha} \beta)|}{|1 - \overline{\alpha} \beta|^2} \\
&= \frac{|-\alpha \beta + \beta - \alpha + \overline{\alpha} \alpha \beta|}{|1 - \overline{\alpha} \beta|^2} \\
&= \frac{|\beta - \alpha (\overline{\alpha} \beta - 1)|}{|1 - \overline{\alpha} \beta|^2} \\
&= \frac{|\beta - \alpha \overline{\beta}|}{|1 - \overline{\alpha} \beta|^2}.
\end{align*}Note that $|\beta - \alpha \overline{\beta}|$ is the distance between $\beta$ and $\alpha \overline{\beta}$ in the complex plane, and $|1 - \overline{\alpha} \beta|^2$ is the square of the distance between 1 and $\overline{\alpha} \beta$ in the complex plane.

