By the triangle inequality,
\[|\beta - \alpha \overline{\beta}| \le |\beta - 1| + |1 - \alpha \overline{\beta}|.\]Since $|\beta| = 1,$ $|\beta - 1| = |\overline{\beta} - 1|,$ so
\[|\beta - \alpha \overline{\beta}| \le |\overline{\beta} - 1| + |1 - \alpha \overline{\beta}|.\]Then by the triangle inequality again,
\[|\beta - \alpha \overline{\beta}| \le |\overline{\beta} - 1| + |\alpha \overline{\beta} - 1| + |\alpha \overline{\beta} - \overline{\alpha} \beta|.\]Since $|\overline{\beta} - 1| = |\beta - 1|,$
\[|\beta - \alpha \overline{\beta}| \le 2 |\beta - 1| + |\alpha \overline{\beta} - 1| + |\alpha \overline{\beta} - \overline{\alpha} \beta|.\]Note that $|\alpha \overline{\beta} - 1| = |\overline{\alpha} \beta - 1|$ is the distance between $\overline{\alpha} \beta$ and 1, and $|\alpha \overline{\beta} - \overline{\alpha} \beta|$ is the distance between $\alpha \overline{\beta}$ and $\overline{\alpha} \beta.$  The maximum value of the expression we want is then $\boxed{2}.$

Equality occurs when $\alpha = 0$ or $\beta = 1.$

